  "summary": "Opus-4-6 delivers a clean, focused todo UI with strong alignment, consistent card styling, and an obvious primary action. The language is plain and familiar, and the form-plus-list layout makes the core add, check, and delete workflow easy to recognize. Its main weaknesses are in feedback and resilience: loading is only lightly indicated, system health relies on a small unlabeled status dot, and preventive validation or undo paths are limited. Visual accessibility also needs attention because secondary gray text and small controls contribute to confirmed contrast and target-size concerns.",
